"title": "4133: demons, possession by",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4133",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A recognised condition in Jesus Christ's lifetime in which an individual is dominated by the influence of a demon. In his ministry, Jesus Christ encountered and delivered many people in such a condition. Many of Christ's critics unsuccessfully sought to ascribe his authority and powers to demonic possession.</p>\n<h2>Unfounded accusations of demon-possession</h2>\n<h3>Against John the Baptist</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:18\">MAT 11:18</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:33\">LUK 7:33</a></p>\n<h3>Against Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:20-John10:21\">JHN 10:20–10:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:34\">MAT 9:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:24\">MAT 12:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:22\">MRK 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:15\">LUK 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:20\">JHN 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:48-John8:52\">JHN 8:48–8:52</a></p>\n<h3>Unfounded accusations of demon-possession against Jesus Christ are refuted</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:25-Matt12:28\">MAT 12:25–12:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:23-Mark3:30\">MRK 3:23–3:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:17-Luke11:20\">LUK 11:17–11:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:21\">JHN 10:21</a></p>\n<h2>Demon-possession arising from sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:9-1Sam18:10\">1SA 18:9–18:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The consequences of demon-possession</h2>\n<h3>Irrational behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10-1Sam18:11\">1SA 18:10–18:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:9-1Sam19:10\">1SA 19:9–19:10</a></p>\n<h3>Unnatural physical strength</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:4\">MRK 5:4</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:28\">MAT 8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:29\">LUK 8:29</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:16\">ACT 19:16</a></p>\n<h3>Self-harm</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:5\">MRK 5:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Violent behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:18\">MRK 9:18</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:39\">LUK 9:39</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:28\">MAT 8:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:3-Mark5:5\">MRK 5:3–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:27-Luke8:29\">LUK 8:27–8:29</a></p>\n<h3>The impairment of faculties</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22\">MAT 12:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:32\">MAT 9:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17\">MRK 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:11\">LUK 13:11</a></p>\n<h3>Suffering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:25-Mark7:26\">MRK 7:25–7:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:14-1Sam16:16\">1SA 16:14–16:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:15\">MAT 17:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:18\">MRK 9:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:39\">LUK 9:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:18\">LUK 6:18</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ delivers from demon-possession</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16\">MAT 8:16</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:32\">MRK 1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:40\">LUK 4:40</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:24\">MAT 4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:32\">MAT 9:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22\">MAT 12:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:25-Mark7:26\">MRK 7:25–7:26</a></p>\n<h2>Multiple demon-possession</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ encounters cases of multiple demon-possession and is able to deliver</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:9\">MRK 16:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:1-Mark5:17\">MRK 5:1–5:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:26-Luke8:35\">LUK 8:26–8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:2\">LUK 8:2</a></p>\n<h3>Further evidence of the possibility of multiple demon-possession</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:43-Matt12:45\">MAT 12:43–12:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:24-Luke11:26\">LUK 11:24–11:26</a></p>\n<h2>Demons recognise divine authority and their own limited powers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:19\">JAS 2:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Demons know Jesus Christ's identity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:24\">MRK 1:24</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:34\">LUK 4:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:29\">MAT 8:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:7\">MRK 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:28\">LUK 8:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:34\">MRK 1:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:11\">MRK 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:15\">ACT 19:15</a></p>\n<h3>Demons recognise Jesus Christ's disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:16-Acts16:17\">ACT 16:16–16:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's disciples have power to release from demon-possession by calling on Jesus' name</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:16\">ACT 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:13-Acts19:16\">ACT 19:13–19:16</a></p>",
